#!/usr/bin/env elixir
# 🛡️ Container Configuration Guardian System
#
# ## Purpose
# Comprehensive protection system to prevent unauthorized changes to container
# configurations, ensuring CLAUDE.md compliance and SOPv5.1 framework adherence.
#
# ## Agent-Friendly Protection Architecture
# Multi-layer protection system:
# 1. **File Integrity Monitoring** - Detects unauthorized configuration changes
# 2. **Change Authorization System** - Requires multiple validation steps
# 3. **Rollback Capabilities** - Automatic restoration of approved configurations
# 4. **Audit Trail Maintenance** - Complete tracking of all configuration changes
# 5. **Real-time Alerts** - Immediate notification of protection violations
#
# ## Protection Mechanisms
# - **Cryptographic Hashing**: SHA-256 checksums for all critical files
# - **Multi-Point Validation**: Multiple checks before allowing changes
# - **Atomic Operations**: All-or-nothing change application
# - **Version Control Integration**: Git-based change tracking
# - **Emergency Recovery**: Rapid restoration from known-good states
#
# ## Integration Points
# - SOPv5.1 cybernetic framework goal validation
# - TPS methodology 5-Level RCA for violations
# - STAMP safety constraint enforcement
# - Container compliance system coordination
# - Agent training and certification systems
#
# Updated: 2025-07-31 09:10:36 CEST
# Version: v1.0.0-guardian-system
# Framework: SOPv5.1 + TPS + STAMP + Multi-Layer Protection

defmodule ContainerConfigGuardian do
  @moduledoc """
  🛡️ Container Configuration Guardian System
  
  Comprehensive protection against unauthorized container configuration changes.
  Implements multi-layer defense with agent-friendly interfaces and integration.
  """

  require Logger

  @protected_files [
    "podman-compose.yml",
    "containers/git-aware-nixos.nix",
    "lib/intelitor/container_compliance.ex",
    "containers/*.nix",
    "scripts/containers/*.exs",
    "CLAUDE.md"  # Ultimate protection for core policy document
  ]

  @protection_config %{
    hash_algorithm: :sha256,
    backup_retention: 30,  # days
    max_daily_changes: 5,
    require_approval_threshold: 3,  # number of approvals needed
    emergency_contacts: ["admin@intelitor.com", "security@intelitor.com"]
  }

  @doc """
  Initializes the Container Configuration Guardian System.
  
  ## Agent Notes
  Sets up complete protection infrastructure:
  - Creates baseline checksums for all protected files
  - Establishes monitoring infrastructure
  - Configures alert systems
  - Validates integration with existing systems
  """
  def initialize_guardian_system(_options \\ []) do
    IO.puts """
    🛡️ CONTAINER CONFIGURATION GUARDIAN INITIALIZATION
    =================================================
    
    Initialization Date: #{DateTime.utc_now() |> DateTime.to_string()}
    Protection Level: Enterprise-Grade Multi-Layer Defense
    Integration: SOPv5.1 + TPS + STAMP + Container Compliance
    
    """

    # Step 1: Create protection infrastructure
    create_protection_infrastructure()
    
    # Step 2: Generate baseline checksums
    generate_baseline_checksums()
    
    # Step 3: Setup monitoring systems
    setup_monitoring_systems()
    
    # Step 4: Configure alert mechanisms
    configure_alert_systems()
    
    # Step 5: Validate integrations
    validate_system_integrations()
    
    # Step 6: Create emergency procedures
    create_emergency_procedures()

    IO.puts """
    
    ✅ GUARDIAN SYSTEM INITIALIZATION COMPLETE
    =========================================
    
    📊 Protection Status:
    • Protected Files: #{length(@protected_files)} files under monitoring
    • Baseline Checksums: #{count_baseline_checksums()} checksums generated
    • Monitoring Active: Real-time change detection enabled
    • Alert Systems: #{count_alert_channels()} channels configured
    • Integration Points: #{count_integrations()} systems integrated
    • Emergency Procedures: Complete recovery system activated
    
    🎯 Guardian System Status: ACTIVE AND PROTECTING ✅
    
    ## Agent Usage Commands
    ```bash
    # Check protection status
    elixir scripts/protection/container_config_guardian.exs --status
    
    # Validate file integrity
    elixir scripts/protection/container_config_guardian.exs --validate
    
    # Request authorized change
    elixir scripts/protection/container_config_guardian.exs --request-change FILE REASON
    
    # Emergency recovery
    elixir scripts/protection/container_config_guardian.exs --emergency-recover
    ```
    """
  end

